9.name: Sparring Gloves
9.description: Gain Critical Strike Chance and Dodge Chance.

11.name: Deathblade
11.description: Contributing to a kill grants the holder addtional Attack Damage for the rest of combat.

12.name: Giant Slayer
12.description: The holder's spells and basic attacks do bonus damage. If the target has more health, the bonus damage increases.

13.name: Hextech Gunblade
13.description: The holder's spells heal them for a percentage of the damage dealt. Excess healing fuels a shield that protects the holder.

14.name: Spear of Shojin
14.description: The holder's basic attacks restore Mana on-hit.

15.name: Guardian Angel
15.description: Prevents the wearer's first death, reviving them after a short delay and sheding all negative effects.

16.name: Bloodthirster
16.description: Basic attacks heal the holder for a percentage of the damage dealt.

17.name: Zeke's Herald
17.description: When combat begins, the wearer and nearby allies in the same row gain Attack Speed for the rest of combat.

18.name: Sword of the Divine
18.description: The holder gains the Divine trait.

19.name: Infinity Edge
19.description: Grants Critical Strike Chance. Each point of Critical Strike Chance above 100% becomes bonus Critical Strike Damage.

22.name: Rapid Firecannon
22.description: The holder gains Attack Range, and their Basic Attacks can't miss.

23.name: Guinsoo's Rageblade
23.description: Basic Attacks grant bonus Attack Speed for the rest of combat.

24.name: Statikk Shiv
24.description: Every third Basic Attack from the wearer deals Magic Damage to nearby enemies, and true damage if they are shielded or crowd-controlled.

25.name: Titan's Resolve
25.description: When the wearer takes damage or inflicts a critical hit, they gain a stacking damage bonus. The damage stacks up to a limit, at which point the wearer gains Armor and Magic Resistance, and increases in size.

26.name: Runaan's Hurricane
26.description: Basic Attacks fire a bolt at another nearby enemy, dealing a percentage of the wearer's Attack Damage and applying on-hit effects. These bolts can critical strike.

27.name: Zz'Rot Portal
27.description: When the wearer dies, a Construct arises to continue the fight.

28.name: Duelist's Zeal
28.description: The holder gains the Duelist trait.

29.name: Last Whisper
29.description: When the wearer inflicts a critical hit, the target's Armor is reduced for a number of seconds.

33.name: Rabadon's Deathcap
33.description: The holder gains additional Spell Power.

34.name: Luden's Echo
34.description: When the holder casts their spell, the first target dealt magic damage and to nearby enemies are dealt additional magic damage.

35.name: Locket of the Iron Solari
35.description: When combat begins, the wearer and nearby allies in the same row gain a shield that blocks damage for several seconds.

36.name: Ionic Spark
36.description: Nearby enemies have their Magic Resist reduced. When they cast a spell, they are zapped taking magic damage equal to a percentage of their max Mana.

37.name: Morellonomicon
37.description: When the holder deals damage with their spell, they burn the target, dealing a percentage of the target's maximum Health as true damage over several seconds, and reducing healing by a percentage for the duration of the burn.

38.name: Spirit of the Dragon
38.description: The holder gains the Dragonsoul trait.

39.name: Jeweled Gauntlet
39.description: The holder's spells can cause critical hits, and the holder gains bonus Critical Strike Damage.

44.name: Blue Buff
44.description: After casting their spell, the wearer gains Mana.

45.name: Frozen Heart
45.description: Reduces the Attack Speed of nearby enemies. Each Frozen Heart a champion carries beyond the first increases the radius of this effect.

46.name: Chalice of Power
46.description: When combat begins, the wearer and all nearby allies in the same row gain Spell Power for the rest of combat.

47.name: Redemption
47.description: When the wearer dies, allies are healed.

48.name: Mage's Hat
48.description: The holder gains the Mage trait.

49.name: Hand Of Justice
49.description: At the beginning of each planning phase, the wearer's basic attacks and spells deal additional damage or heal for a percentage of damage dealt.

55.name: Bramble Vest
55.description: Negates bonus damage from incoming critical hits. On being hit by a Basic Attack, deal magic damage to all nearby enemies.

56.name: Gargoyle Stoneplate
56.description: The holder gains Armor and Magic Resist for each enemy targeting them.

57.name: Sunfire Cape
57.description: At start of combat, and every couple seconds thereafter, a random nearby enemyis burned for a percentage of their maximum health. Any healing they receive is reduced.

58.name: Vanguard's Cuirass
58.description: The holder gains the Vanguard trait.

59.name: Shroud of Stillness
59.description: When combat begins, shoots a beam straight ahead that delays affected enemies' first spellcast, increasing their max Mana until they cast.

67.name: Zephyr
67.description: When combat begins, the wearer summons a whirlwind on the opposite side of the arena that removes the closest enemy from combat for several seconds.

68.name: Elderwood Sprout
68.description: The holder gains the Elderwood trait.

69.name: Quicksilver
69.description: The wearer is immune to crowd control for the first several seconds of combat.

78.name: Warlord's Banner
78.description: The wearer gains the Warlord trait.

79.name: Trap Claw
79.description: Blocks the first enemy spell that hits the wearer, and stuns the spell's caster for several seconds.

89.name: Youmuu's Ghostblade
89.description: The wearer gains the Assassin trait.

99.name: Thief's Gloves
99.description: At the beginning of each planning phase, the wearer equips 2 temporary items. Temporary items increase in power based on your player level.

9001.name: Anima Visage
9001.description: The wearer regenerates a percentage of their maximum Health each second.

9002.name: Death's Defiance
9002.description: A percentage of the damage the wearer receives is instead dealt over time as non-lethal damage.

9003.name: Eternal Winter
9003.description: Enemies who damage the wearer have their Attack Speed slowed for several seconds. After being slowed this way a certain number of times, the attacker is Frozen for the duration instead. An enemy can only be Frozen once every several seconds.

9005.name: Manazane
9005.description: After the wearer casts their spell for the first time each combat, they restore Mana over several seconds.

9006.name: Obsidian Cleaver
9006.description: The wearer's attacks and spell damage shred enemy Armor and Magic Resistance by 40% for several seconds.

9007.name: Randuin's Sanctum
9007.description: At the start of combat, all allies adjacent to the wearer gain bonus Armor and Magic Resistance for the rest of combat.

9008.name: Rocket-Propelled Fist
9008.description: At the start of combat, the wearer pulls the farthest enemy into melee range, stunning them for several seconds. Allies within range will prioritize attacking that enemy.

9009.name: Gold Collector
9009.description: The wearer executes enemies below a percentage of health on hit. Executions generate 1 gold.

9010.name: Zhonya's Paradox
9010.description: The first instance of damage that would reduce the wearer below a percentage of their Health is prevented, causing them to become invulnerable for several seconds.
